{{About|a music journal|the more general distinction between theory and practice|Theory}}
{{Notability|Products|date=May 2012}}
{{Italic title}}
'''''Theory and Practice''''' ({{ISSN|0741-6156}}) is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] specializing in [[music theory]] and [[musical analysis|analysis]]. It is the annual journal of the [[Music Theory Society of New York State]], which was "[t]he first regional theory organization" in the United States, having "held its initial meeting in 1971 at the Eastman School of Music."<ref>[[David Carson Berry]], "[http://www.gmth.de/zeitschrift/artikel/206.aspx Schenkerian Theory in the United States: A Review of Its Establishment and a Survey of Current Research Topics]", ''Zeitschrift der Gesellschaft für Musiktheorie'' 2/2–3 (2005), 112.</ref> The journal began publication in 1975, initially with the subtitle "''Newsletter-Journal of the Music Theory Society of New York State''".

The journal is currently [[editor in chief|edited]] by Sarah Marlowe and Brian Moseley. Recent past editors include Matthew Brown, (2012–2015), Seth Monahan and Matt BaileyShea (2009–2011), Adrian Childs (2007-2008), Philip Stoecker (2005–07), [[David Carson Berry]] (2003–04), Mark Anson-Cartwright (1999-2002), and Taylor A. Greer (1997–99).

